  <prompt>
    Create the Field Mapping Profile table (sprk_fieldmappingprofile) in Dataverse. This table stores
    mapping configurations between source and target entities, enabling admin-configurable field
    inheritance. The table must support the Field Mapping Framework requirements for N:1 and N:N
    relationship mappings that Dataverse OOB does not provide.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer with expertise in Dataverse solution customization and table design.
    Follow ADRs strictly. Understand Power Platform schema conventions and relationship modeling.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Field Mapping Profile table created in Dataverse with all required fields, configured for the
    Spaarke solution. Table should be visible in model-driven app navigation.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The Field Mapping Framework enables admin-configurable field-to-field mappings between parent
      and child entities. This addresses Dataverse OOB mapping limitations (1:N only). The Profile
      table defines which entity pairs have mappings; individual field mappings are stored in the
      related Rule table (task 002).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/events-and-workflow-automation-r1/spec.md - Data Model section</file>
      <file>src/solutions/ - Existing Dataverse solutions</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">Table name: sprk_fieldmappingprofile</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Must include: Name, Source Entity, Target Entity, Description, Is Active, Sync Mode</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Sync Mode choice values: One-time (0), Manual Refresh (1), Update Related (2)</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No Dataverse Business Rules - validation in code only</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/plugins.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>projects/events-and-workflow-automation-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Dataverse Table Creation" location=".claude/patterns/dataverse/">
        Standard pattern for creating Dataverse tables with proper naming and configuration
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Review spec.md Data Model section for Field Mapping Profile table schema</step>
    <step order="2">Open Dataverse maker portal or use PAC CLI to create the table</step>
    <step order="3">Create sprk_fieldmappingprofile table with display name "Field Mapping Profile"</step>
    <step order="4">Add Name field (primary, text, max 200 chars, required)</step>
    <step order="5">Add Source Entity field (text, max 100 chars, required) - logical name of source</step>
    <step order="6">Add Target Entity field (text, max 100 chars, required) - logical name of target</step>
    <step order="7">Add Description field (memo, optional)</step>
    <step order="8">Add Is Active field (boolean, default true)</step>
    <step order="9">Add Sync Mode field (choice: One-time=0, Manual Refresh=1, Update Related=2)</step>
    <step order="10">Configure table for model-driven app visibility</step>
    <step order="11">Add table to Spaarke solution</step>
    <step order="12">Export and verify solution XML</step>
    <step order="13">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 001 status to âœ… completed</step>
    <step order="14">Document any deviations in projects/events-and-workflow-automation-r1/notes/</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="pac">Power Platform CLI for Dataverse operations</tool>
    <tool name="terminal">Run shell commands</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="dataverse">sprk_fieldmappingprofile table in Dataverse</output>
    <output type="solution">Updated Spaarke solution with new table</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given the Dataverse environment, when I navigate to Tables, then sprk_fieldmappingprofile
      exists with all specified fields.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given the Field Mapping Profile table, when I create a new record, then all required fields
      (Name, Source Entity, Target Entity) are enforced.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given the Sync Mode field, when I open the dropdown, then options One-time, Manual Refresh,
      and Update Related are available.
    </criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The Source Entity and Target Entity fields store logical names (e.g., "sprk_matter", "sprk_event")
    rather than display names. This allows programmatic lookup of entity metadata.

    Do not create Business Rules for validation - all validation happens in the PCF control and API.
  </notes>

